法規內容.條文內容:
To be acknowledged as having "obtained an equivalent educational level" as referred to in Paragraph 1 of Article 4 of the Law, a person must possess one of the following qualifications:
1. have completed the third-year courses in a public or private junior high school　　　or in a school providing the equivalent of a junior high school education, and holds a certificate of study attesting to this fact;
2. have completed coursework in a supplementary compulsory school attached to a public or private junior high school, or in a government-accredited private secondary supplementary school, and holds a course completion certificate;
3. have passed a junior high school equivalency examination, and holds an equivalency certificate; or 
4. hold a Class C technician's certificate, or possesses a technician's certificate that confers qualifications equivalent to level C or higher.
